<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-07-15T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-07-15T06:00:00-05:00" n="322" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d322">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/22896:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Casablanca (<persName type="from">Russell</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Casablanca</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-07-15T12:00:00+01:00">July
                                        15, 1942—noon.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received 12:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>543. German Commission has started control of commercial vessels
                                arriving in port. On Dakar convoy all soldiers disembarked
                                immediately on ships coming alongside quays paraded and were
                                inspected <pb facs="0345" n="339" xml:id="pg_339"/> by Commission.
                                Ships’ officers much annoyed by arbitrary manner in which this
                                complete control exercised.</p>
                            <p>Repeated to Algiers, by courier to Tangier.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>